<L>__{48. wide on the battle}
<A>__{to see the two ships about to pass abreast, the surprise heading south as it were, the enemy ship, north. the french vessel is clearly the bigger ship, and from both come the sounds of shouted orders and the thunder of drums. they will pass broadside to broadside, 500 yards apart.}
